  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "De 5:1-29. A Commemoration of the Covenant in Horeb.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. Hear, O Israel, the statutes and judgments—Whether this rehearsal of the law was made in a solemn assembly, or as some think at a general meeting of the elders as representatives of the people, is of little moment; it was addressed either directly or indirectly to the Hebrew people as principles of their peculiar constitution as a nation; and hence, as has been well observed, \"the Jewish law has no obligation upon Christians, unless so much of it as given or commanded by Jesus Christ; for whatever in this law is conformable to the laws of nature, obliges us, not as given by Moses, but by virtue of an antecedent law common to all rational beings\" [Bishop Wilson].God, upon Mount Horeb, makes a covenant with Israel,  Deu 5:1-5. The covenant or ten commandments is delivered to Moses in two tables,  Deu 5:6-22. The Israelites desire that not God, but Moses, may speak to them,  Deu 5:23-27; which God approves of,  Deu 5:28-31. Moses exhorts them to obedience, with a pro mise of life,  Deu 5:32,33.  Moses called all Israel,  to wit, by their elders, who were to impart it to the rest. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "1. Hear, O Israel, the statutes and judgments—Whether this rehearsal of the law was made in a solemn assembly, or as some think at a general meeting of the elders as representatives of the people, is of little moment; it was addressed either directly or indirectly to the Hebrew people as principles of their peculiar constitution as a nation; and hence, as has been well observed, \"the Jewish law has no obligation upon Christians, unless so much of it as given or commanded by Jesus Christ; for whatever in this law is conformable to the laws of nature, obliges us, not as given by Moses, but by virtue of an antecedent law common to all rational beings\" [Bishop Wilson].God, upon Mount Horeb, makes a covenant with Israel, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 5:1-5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The covenant or ten commandments is delivered to Moses in two tables, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 5:6-22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The Israelites desire that not God, but Moses, may speak to them, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 5:23-27",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; which God approves of, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 5:28-31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Moses exhorts them to obedience, with a pro mise of life, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 5:32,33",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Moses called all Israel, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " to wit, by their elders, who were to impart it to the rest. ",
