    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 5:1-5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " form the introduction, and point out the importance and great significance of the exposition which follows. Hence, instead of the simple sentence \"And Moses said,\" we have the more formal statement \"And Moses called all Israel, and said to them.\" The great significance of the laws and rights about to be set before them, consisted in the fact that they contained the covenant of Jehovah with Israel.",
